definitions.definition: The point where two converging lines meet; an angle , either external or internal.
examples: The corners of the wire mesh were reinforced with little blobs of solder.

subdefinitions.definition: The space in the angle between converging lines or walls which meet in a point.
examples: The chimney corner was full of cobwebs.

subdefinitions.definition: The projection into space of an angle in a solid object.
examples: Herbert bruised his shin on the corner of the coffee table.

subdefinitions.definition: An intersection of two streets; any of the four outer points off the street at that intersection.
examples: The liquor store on the corner also sold lottery tickets.

subdefinitions.definition: ( Maine ) The neighborhood surrounding an intersection of rural roads.
( attributive ) Denoting a premises that is in a convenient local location, notionally, but not necessarily literally, on the corner of two streets.
examples: corner store , corner deli , corner newsagent

definitions.definition: An edge or extremity ; the part farthest from the center; hence, any quarter or part, or the direction in which it lies.
examples: Shining a light in the dark corners of the mind. I took a trip out to his corner of town.

definitions.definition: A secret or secluded place; a remote or out of the way place; a nook .
examples: On weekends, Emily liked to find a quiet corner and curl up with a good book.

definitions.definition: ( business , finance ) A sufficient interest in a salable security or commodity to allow the cornering party to influence prices.
examples: In the 1970s, private investors tried to get a corner on the silver market, but were ultimately unsuccessful.

subdefinitions.definition: ( figuratively ) Complete control or ownership of something.

definitions.definition: ( heading ) Relating to the playing field.

subdefinitions.definition: ( baseball ) One of the four vertices of the strike zone .
examples: The pitch was just off the corner , low and outside.

subdefinitions.definition: ( baseball ) First base or third base .
examples: There are runners on the corners with just one out.

subdefinitions.definition: ( boxing ) The corner of the ring , which is where the boxer rests before and during a fight.
( boxing , by extension ) The group of people who assist a boxer during a bout .

definitions.definition: A place where people meet for a particular purpose.
( obsolete ) A point scored in a rubber at whist .
